2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses detailed network simulations to understand the economic implications of resource sharing, which involves the use of information theory concepts. 
3. cs.GT (Game Theory) - The paper analyzes the economic implications of resource sharing in a vertically differentiated duopoly market, which involves game theory concepts. 
4. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper uses network simulations to understand the economic implications of resource sharing, which falls under the domain of computational engineering, finance, and science. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the technical properties of millimeter wave bands, which are used for multimedia applications such as high-speed data transfer and video streaming.
